[BID 1N] You have a balanced 15-17, so open 1NT and describe the hand at once. Partner then decides the final contract. Your partner bids 2\C, Stayman, asking opener for a four-card major. It carries enough strength to act, regardless of clubs.
[BID 2D] You lack a four-card major, so reply 2\D. The denial nudges the auction toward notrump. Your partner sees the 2\D denial and, with game-going values and no major fit, bids 3NT. The hands together hold enough for game without an eight-card major.
[BID Pass] You pass; 3NT is the final contract.
[show NS]The 2\D denial showed no major, so 3NT was the right resting place. South opened 1NT with \SKT5 \HA7 \DKJ9 \CA9875, and the long club suit headed by the ace provided the extra tricks for nine.}
